The winters in England are gene. rally too severe, to suffer olive-trees to be. planted in the open ground. The way of propagating them here is by laying down their tendet branchos, and taking them from the mother-plant in about two years. This method is so tedious, that most people choose to have them from Italy in the spring. They are usually planted in pots or cases, and removed into the green-house at the approach of winter.
